@startuml Collaboration Diagram - CORRECTED
!theme plain
title University Timetabling Solver - Communication Diagram (Actual Structure)

actor User

rectangle "Timetabling System" {
    
    object "run_solver.py" as Runner <<Entry Point>>
    object "itc2019_parser.py" as Parser <<Parser Module>>
    object "SolveConfig" as Config <<Dataclass>>
    object "Instance" as Instance <<Data Dict>>
    object "solver_cp_sat.py" as Solver <<Solver Module>>
    object "CpModel" as Model <<OR-Tools>>
    object "CpSolver" as CPSolver <<OR-Tools>>
    object "SolutionResult" as Result <<Data Dict>>
    object "full_solution.json" as JSON <<Output>>
    object "index.html" as Dashboard <<Web UI>>
}

' Numbered message flow
User -(1)-> Runner : execute
Runner -(2)-> Parser : parse_itc2019_xml_to_instance()
Parser -(3)-> Instance : creates dict
Runner -(4)-> Config : create SolveConfig()
Runner -(5)-> Solver : solve_instance(instance, config)
Solver -(6)-> Model : create CpModel()
Solver -(7)-> CPSolver : create CpSolver()
Solver -(8)-> CPSolver : solve() [lexicographic stages]
Solver -(9)-> Solver : solve_instance_lns() [if enabled]
Solver -(10)-> Result : produces dict
Runner -(11)-> Solver : validate_solution()
Runner -(12)-> JSON : save dict
Runner -(13)-> Dashboard : launch browser view
User -(14)-> Dashboard : view results

' Self-messages / internal calls
Solver -(8a)-> Solver : _estimate_class_demand()
Solver -(8b)-> Solver : _add_schedule_hints()
Solver -(8c)-> Solver : Add constraints (in-line)

note right of Runner
  Entry point module with
  main(), _summarize(),
  _print_examiner_output()
end note

note right of Solver
  Solver module with functions:
  - solve_instance()
  - solve_instance_lns()
  - validate_solution()
  - _add_schedule_hints()
  - _estimate_class_demand()
  ~800 lines total
end note

note right of Parser
  Parser module with:
  - parse_itc2019_xml_to_instance()
  - _build_time_domain()
  - _collect_rooms()
  - _parse_students()
end note

note bottom of Result
  Plain dictionary with:
  status, schedule, students,
  objectives, baseline/lns metrics
end note

@enduml
